visitLocationComments: Impossible to miss, massive pool surrounded by rocky outcroppings just off roadside. Back of pool is private land and completely inaccessible. Posted as H. Bergantino, Grant posted across the road.
visitHabitatOther: Some sap lines, possible minor logging behind vernal pool
visitHabitatComment: Steep ravine to the side of vernal pool, steep ridge on other side of road.
visitSpeciesComments: Hundreds of different egg masses. Wood Frogs, Spotted Salamanders, and either blue or hybrid salamander eggs (lots of white eggs in those masses). The road side of the vernal pool is also the sunniest, and nearly the entire length along the edge was full of egg masses attached to submerged branches, leaves, etc. No fish seen at all, but the edges were teeming with Red-Spotted Newts. Tons of aquatic beetles, Caddisfly larvae.
reviewQANotes: Significant pool with long hydroperiod and Jeff/Blue-spotted unisexuals.
